Name: lijo
Review: Review of a wonderful movie which i have watched today The movie , Take Off, (Malayalam) is a real portryal of the True life of a middle class Nurse . A great thank to Mr.Mahesh Naryan (Director ) that he has choosen the life of a suffering middle class Nurse in order to picturise a real life experience , which our Big celebrities and other cultural personalities often forget or ignore to do it . I feel the great survival of a Nurse always attained either she or he always passes through such onerous and abominable life circumstances or it could be continuous struggling , which usually not happens the life of other professionals.Very unsupportive financial status of the family, bank loans , responsibilities toward siblings and parents etc..always puts a Nurse in life where she or he always forget to live themselves. This movie has given me a great principle that the life will be succeded one day ...and also why the American or European people salute or give an offical diginity to a Regesterd Nurse ...even the Indian medical community has not known it ...Thank you the team of Take Off movie , once again that you have awaken the Malayalam movie from the great hibernation of imaginations or world of fictions or from a world of amorphous concepts ...Parvathi...has done a brilliant acting...Pls Dont forget to see the movie .

Title: a movie well taken

Name: Noble
Review: It’s not always that a movie leaves the viewers with their hearts heavy. It takes genuineness and intensity of situations to do that. Take off, through its impeccable execution of a heavy weight theme gifts the viewers an enthralling emotional experience.Reality is far from being real unless it is experiences firsthand. Take off is inspired by a true story which occurred in the recent past, when a group of Nurses in Iraq were abducted by ISIS terrorists. The news was indeed an impactful one, but it just passed as another impactful news. Take off takes the viewers to the hot seat located at the heart of the battle field, right where the nurses were. The movie from its outset itself establishes a firm emotional connect with the lead character Sameera, which proves to be the driving force for the viewers to relate with her throughout.

Name: Tom
Review: Take Off:A movie, which malayali audience never expects from our Mallu Film Industry...What a movie! and what a thrilling 2nd half. Fahad, this movie is for u...even if you only have role in second half...Parvathi was not acting in this film...Super performance Fahad and Parvathi??Heard that it was shooted in RAK, the scence of Iraq, but well shooted without any defect. The crew has taken few real videos of Iraq from the medias like CNN and BBC etc i think, even though, it was well edited. The subject of the movie was the evacuation of Malayali nurses from Iraq in 2014. Many of us had thought and discussed, why these nurses left to Iraq for job even they know the risk involved in that job. This movie is the answer for that.Me and my cousin Martin had seen the shooting of this movie in last August when it was shooted in Sree Narayana Medical College, Chalaka(nearby our home). we met Kunjakko and all there. The name fixed for this movie that time was MALE NURSE. We never thought this movie will be good one as it is. Hatsoff to director debutant Mr. Mahesh Narayanan...A good watch...

Name: Vasundhara Krishnan
Review: The movie has been directed exceptionally well and has tried its best to show the life of a female nurse; her responsibilities, the sacrifices she makes in order to make a living, etc. More wonderful is the way the movie has been shot; interspersed with flashbacks, real footage of war-torn Iraq, etc. nnFor a Malayalam movie, this is a 'must watch.' It becomes even more interesting to think that around 50 nurses underwent the same conditions like that in the movie, two years back. The beauty of the movie lies in its effort to make it seem more realistic than fictional.

Name: lijo
Review: Review of a wonderful movie which i have watched today The movie , Take Off, (Malayalam) is a real portryal of the True life of a middle class Nurse . A great thank to Mr.Mahesh Naryan (Director ) that he has choosen the life of a suffering middle class Nurse in order to picturise a real life experience , which our Big celebrities and other cultural personalities often forget or ignore to do it . I feel the great survival of a Nurse always attained either she or he always passes through such onerous and abominable life circumstances or it could be continuous struggling , which usually not happens the life of other professionals.Very unsupportive financial status of the family, bank loans , responsibilities toward siblings and parents etc..always puts a Nurse in life where she or he always forget to live themselves. This movie has given me a great principle that the life will be succeded one day ...and also why the American or European people salute or give an offical diginity to a Regesterd Nurse ...even the Indian medical community has not known it ...Thank you the team of Take Off movie , once again that you have awaken the Malayalam movie from the great hibernation of imaginations or world of fictions or from a world of amorphous concepts ...Parvathi...has done a brilliant acting...Pls Dont forget to see the movie .

Title: a movie well taken

Name: Noble
Review: It’s not always that a movie leaves the viewers with their hearts heavy. It takes genuineness and intensity of situations to do that. Take off, through its impeccable execution of a heavy weight theme gifts the viewers an enthralling emotional experience.Reality is far from being real unless it is experiences firsthand. Take off is inspired by a true story which occurred in the recent past, when a group of Nurses in Iraq were abducted by ISIS terrorists. The news was indeed an impactful one, but it just passed as another impactful news. Take off takes the viewers to the hot seat located at the heart of the battle field, right where the nurses were. The movie from its outset itself establishes a firm emotional connect with the lead character Sameera, which proves to be the driving force for the viewers to relate with her throughout.

Name: Tom
Review: Take Off:A movie, which malayali audience never expects from our Mallu Film Industry...What a movie! and what a thrilling 2nd half. Fahad, this movie is for u...even if you only have role in second half...Parvathi was not acting in this film...Super performance Fahad and Parvathi??Heard that it was shooted in RAK, the scence of Iraq, but well shooted without any defect. The crew has taken few real videos of Iraq from the medias like CNN and BBC etc i think, even though, it was well edited. The subject of the movie was the evacuation of Malayali nurses from Iraq in 2014. Many of us had thought and discussed, why these nurses left to Iraq for job even they know the risk involved in that job. This movie is the answer for that.Me and my cousin Martin had seen the shooting of this movie in last August when it was shooted in Sree Narayana Medical College, Chalaka(nearby our home). we met Kunjakko and all there. The name fixed for this movie that time was MALE NURSE. We never thought this movie will be good one as it is. Hatsoff to director debutant Mr. Mahesh Narayanan...A good watch...

Title: super

Name: Vasundhara Krishnan
Review: The movie has been directed exceptionally well and has tried its best to show the life of a female nurse; her responsibilities, the sacrifices she makes in order to make a living, etc. More wonderful is the way the movie has been shot; interspersed with flashbacks, real footage of war-torn Iraq, etc. nnFor a Malayalam movie, this is a 'must watch.' It becomes even more interesting to think that around 50 nurses underwent the same conditions like that in the movie, two years back. The beauty of the movie lies in its effort to make it seem more realistic than fictional.
